This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with image and video inpainting. It also involves the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. 

The paper also involves optimization techniques to improve the speed and quality of the inpainting process, which falls under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. 

Furthermore, the paper deals with video inpainting, which falls under the Multimedia (cs.MM) category. 

Finally, the paper involves the use of temporal cues in video inpainting, which falls under the Graphics (cs.GR) category.
